                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "Domain Accounts represent In The Matrix's third-highest frequency technique at 35 reports — the actor obtains and abuses Active Directory domain credentials to authenticate to internal services and remote access infrastructure. Domain account access enables broader lateral movement across the AD environment, GPO-based actions, and Kerberos ticket abuse (T1558), substantially expanding the actor's reach compared to local-only credential use."
                ],
